Date: 20/3/1933
Source: NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page: 182
Edition:
Quote: Light land is more quickly broken in than a stiff heavy soil; it is much easier to manage at any time, and is usually warm and "early". But it is very "hungry" - that is, it consumes humus and other manures quickly.
